  "title": "SOFTWARE DEVELOPER",
  "description": "<ul><li>The primary work comprises of software development.</li><li>Analysis and technical design, including helping Business and System Analyst during requirements gathering.</li><li>Coding and code review.</li><li>Perform unit test and System Integration Testing (SIT).</li><li>Train and support testers during the testing phase, including making bugfixes</li><li>Support User Acceptance Testing (UAT).</li><li>Deploy to production, including releases outside of office hours.</li><li>Post implementation support and technical documentation.</li><li>Investigation and resolving incidents escalated from L1 production support team.</li><li>Pre-Test and actual (Disaster Recovery) RDR development support.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Java – strong command of object-oriented programming, multithreading and performance tuning. Familiarity with working in a full stack capacity within an agile team.</li><li>Ideally have worked on both front-end and server-side.</li><li>Knowledge of Spring framework.</li><li>RESTful API development.</li><li>Experience with relational databases, especially Oracle.</li><li>Comfortable using Maven, Git and Bitbucket.</li><li>10 or more years of relevant experience and implementation</li><li>Optional: JavaScript.</li><li>Optional: Knowledge of ReactJS or another popular JS framework.</li><li>Core Java</li><li>Testing & quality assurance</li><li>Problem-solving & analytical thinking</li></ul>",
